33// Setup for Windows DLL export/import. When building the V8 DLL the
34// BUILDING_V8_SHARED needs to be defined. When building a program which uses
35// the V8 DLL USING_V8_SHARED needs to be defined. When either building the V8
36// static library or building a program which uses the V8 static library neither
37// BUILDING_V8_SHARED nor USING_V8_SHARED should be defined.
38#ifdef BUILDING_V8_SHARED
39# define V8_EXPORT __declspec(dllexport)
40#elif USING_V8_SHARED
41# define V8_EXPORT __declspec(dllimport)
42#else
43# define V8_EXPORT
44#endif // BUILDING_V8_SHARED
45
46#else // V8_OS_WIN
47
48// Setup for Linux shared library export.
49#if V8_HAS_ATTRIBUTE_VISIBILITY
50# ifdef BUILDING_V8_SHARED
51# define V8_EXPORT __attribute__ ((visibility("default")))
52# else
53# define V8_EXPORT
54# endif
55#else
56# define V8_EXPORT
57#endif
58
59#endif // V8_OS_WIN

161class UniqueId {
162 public:
163 explicit UniqueId(intptr_t data)
164 : data_(data) {}
165
166 bool operator==(const UniqueId& other) const {
167 return data_ == other.data_;
168 }
169
170 bool operator!=(const UniqueId& other) const {
171 return data_ != other.data_;
172 }
173
174 bool operator<(const UniqueId& other) const {
175 return data_ < other.data_;
176 }
177
178 private:
179 intptr_t data_;
180};

184#define TYPE_CHECK(T, S) \
185 while (false) { \
186 *(static_cast<T* volatile*>(0)) = static_cast<S*>(0); \

215template <class T>
216class Local {
217 public:
218 V8_INLINE Local() : val_(0) {}
219 template <class S>
220 V8_INLINE Local(Local<S> that)
221 : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
227 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
228 }
229
233 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == 0; }
234
238 V8_INLINE void Clear() { val_ = 0; }
239
240 V8_INLINE T* operator->() const { return val_; }
241
242 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return val_; }
243
250 template <class S>
251 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Local<S>& that) const {
252 internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
253 internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
254 if (a == 0) return b == 0;
255 if (b == 0) return false;
256 return *a == *b;
257 }
258
259 template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator==(
260 const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
261 internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
262 internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
263 if (a == 0) return b == 0;
264 if (b == 0) return false;
265 return *a == *b;
266 }
267
274 template <class S>
275 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Local<S>& that) const {
276 return !operator==(that);
277 }
278
279 template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator!=(
280 const Persistent<S>& that) const {
281 return !operator==(that);
282 }
283
284 template <class S> V8_INLINE static Local<T> Cast(Local<S> that) {
285#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
286 // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
287 // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
288 if (that.IsEmpty()) return Local<T>();
289#endif
290 return Local<T>(T::Cast(*that));
291 }
292
293 template <class S>
294 V8_INLINE Local<S> As() const {
295 return Local<S>::Cast(*this);
296 }
297
303 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, Local<T> that);
304 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate,
305 const PersistentBase<T>& that);
306
307 private:
308 friend class Utils;
309 template<class F> friend class Eternal;
310 template<class F> friend class PersistentBase;
311 template<class F, class M> friend class Persistent;
312 template<class F> friend class Local;
313 template <class F>
314 friend class MaybeLocal;
315 template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
316 template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
317 friend class String;
318 friend class Object;
319 friend class Context;
320 friend class Private;
321 template<class F> friend class internal::CustomArguments;
322 friend Local<Primitive> Undefined(Isolate* isolate);
323 friend Local<Primitive> Null(Isolate* isolate);
324 friend Local<Boolean> True(Isolate* isolate);
325 friend Local<Boolean> False(Isolate* isolate);
326 friend class HandleScope;
327 friend class EscapableHandleScope;
328 template <class F1, class F2, class F3>
329 friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
330 template<class F1, class F2> friend class PersistentValueVector;
331 template <class F>
332 friend class ReturnValue;
333
334 explicit V8_INLINE Local(T* that) : val_(that) {}
335 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, T* that);
336 T* val_;
337};

357template <class T>
358class MaybeLocal {
359 public:
360 V8_INLINE MaybeLocal() : val_(nullptr) {}
361 template <class S>
362 V8_INLINE MaybeLocal(Local<S> that)
363 : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
364 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
365 }
366
367 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
368
369 template <class S>
370 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool ToLocal(Local<S>* out) const {
371 out->val_ = IsEmpty() ? nullptr : this->val_;
372 return !IsEmpty();
373 }
374
375 // Will crash if the MaybeLocal<> is empty.
376 V8_INLINE Local<T> ToLocalChecked();
377
378 template <class S>
379 V8_INLINE Local<S> FromMaybe(Local<S> default_value) const {
380 return IsEmpty() ? default_value : Local<S>(val_);
381 }
382
383 private:
384 T* val_;
385};

388// Eternal handles are set-once handles that live for the life of the isolate.
389template <class T> class Eternal {
390 public:
391 V8_INLINE Eternal() : index_(kInitialValue) { }
392 template<class S>
393 V8_INLINE Eternal(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> handle) : index_(kInitialValue) {
394 Set(isolate, handle);
395 }
396 // Can only be safely called if already set.
397 V8_INLINE Local<T> Get(Isolate* isolate);
398 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() { return index_ == kInitialValue; }
399 template<class S> V8_INLINE void Set(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> handle);
400
401 private:
402 static const int kInitialValue = -1;
403 int index_;
404};

407static const int kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
408
409
410template <typename T>
411class WeakCallbackInfo {
412 public:
413 typedef void (*Callback)(const WeakCallbackInfo<T>& data);
414
415 WeakCallbackInfo(Isolate* isolate, T* parameter,
416 void* internal_fields[kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback],
417 Callback* callback)
418 : isolate_(isolate), parameter_(parameter), callback_(callback) {
419 for (int i = 0; i < kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback; ++i) {
420 internal_fields_[i] = internal_fields[i];
421 }
422 }
423
424 V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const { return isolate_; }
425 V8_INLINE T* GetParameter() const { return parameter_; }
426 V8_INLINE void* GetInternalField(int index) const;
427
428 V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATED("use indexed version",
429 void* GetInternalField1() const) {
430 return internal_fields_[0];
431 }
432 V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATED("use indexed version",
433 void* GetInternalField2() const) {
434 return internal_fields_[1];
435 }
436
437 V8_DEPRECATED("Not realiable once SetSecondPassCallback() was used.",
438 bool IsFirstPass() const) {
439 return callback_ != nullptr;
440 }
441
442 // When first called, the embedder MUST Reset() the Global which triggered the
443 // callback. The Global itself is unusable for anything else. No v8 other api
444 // calls may be called in the first callback. Should additional work be
445 // required, the embedder must set a second pass callback, which will be
446 // called after all the initial callbacks are processed.
447 // Calling SetSecondPassCallback on the second pass will immediately crash.
448 void SetSecondPassCallback(Callback callback) const { *callback_ = callback; }
449
450 private:
451 Isolate* isolate_;
452 T* parameter_;
453 Callback* callback_;
454 void* internal_fields_[kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback];
455};
456
457
458// kParameter will pass a void* parameter back to the callback, kInternalFields
459// will pass the first two internal fields back to the callback, kFinalizer
460// will pass a void* parameter back, but is invoked before the object is
461// actually collected, so it can be resurrected. In the last case, it is not
462// possible to request a second pass callback.
463enum class WeakCallbackType { kParameter, kInternalFields, kFinalizer };
464
478template <class T> class PersistentBase {
479 public:
484 V8_INLINE void Reset();
489 template <class S>
490 V8_INLINE void Reset(Isolate* isolate, const Local<S>& other);
491
496 template <class S>
497 V8_INLINE void Reset(Isolate* isolate, const PersistentBase<S>& other);
498
499 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == NULL; }
500 V8_INLINE void Empty() { val_ = 0; }
501
502 V8_INLINE Local<T> Get(Isolate* isolate) const {
503 return Local<T>::New(isolate, *this);
504 }
505
506 template <class S>
507 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
508 internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
509 internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
510 if (a == NULL) return b == NULL;
511 if (b == NULL) return false;
512 return *a == *b;
513 }
514
515 template <class S>
516 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Local<S>& that) const {
517 internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
518 internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
519 if (a == NULL) return b == NULL;
520 if (b == NULL) return false;
521 return *a == *b;
522 }
523
524 template <class S>
525 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
526 return !operator==(that);
527 }
528
529 template <class S>
530 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Local<S>& that) const {
531 return !operator==(that);
532 }

541 template <typename P>
542 V8_INLINE void SetWeak(P* parameter,

553 V8_INLINE void SetWeak();

556 V8_INLINE P* ClearWeak();

566 V8_INLINE void RegisterExternalReference(Isolate* isolate) const;

581 V8_INLINE void MarkActive();

604 void operator=(const PersistentBase&) = delete;
605
606 private:

609 template<class F> friend class Local;

614 template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
615 template <class F1, class F2, class F3>
616 friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
617 template<class F1, class F2> friend class PersistentValueVector;
618 friend class Object;
619
620 explicit V8_INLINE PersistentBase(T* val) : val_(val) {}
621 V8_INLINE static T* New(Isolate* isolate, T* that);
622
623 T* val_;
624};

674template <class T, class M> class Persistent : public PersistentBase<T> {
675 public:
679 V8_INLINE Persistent() : PersistentBase<T>(0) { }
685 template <class S>
686 V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
687 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
688 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
689 }
695 template <class S, class M2>
696 V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, const Persistent<S, M2>& that)
697 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
698 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
699 }
706 V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
707 Copy(that);
708 }
709 template <class S, class M2>
710 V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
711 Copy(that);
712 }
713 V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent& that) { // NOLINT
714 Copy(that);
715 return *this;
716 }
717 template <class S, class M2>
718 V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) { // NOLINT
719 Copy(that);
720 return *this;
721 }
727 V8_INLINE ~Persistent() {
728 if (M::kResetInDestructor) this->Reset();
729 }
730
731 // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
732 template <class S>
733 V8_INLINE static Persistent<T>& Cast(const Persistent<S>& that) { // NOLINT
734#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
735 // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
736 // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
737 if (!that.IsEmpty()) T::Cast(*that);
738#endif
739 return reinterpret_cast<Persistent<T>&>(const_cast<Persistent<S>&>(that));
740 }
741
742 // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
743 template <class S>
744 V8_INLINE Persistent<S>& As() const { // NOLINT
745 return Persistent<S>::Cast(*this);
746 }
747
748 private:
749 friend class Isolate;
750 friend class Utils;
751 template<class F> friend class Local;
752 template<class F1, class F2> friend class Persistent;
753 template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
754
755 explicit V8_INLINE Persistent(T* that) : PersistentBase<T>(that) {}
756 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
757 template<class S, class M2>
758 V8_INLINE void Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that);
759};

767template <class T>
768class Global : public PersistentBase<T> {
769 public:
773 V8_INLINE Global() : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {}
779 template <class S>
780 V8_INLINE Global(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
781 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
782 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
783 }
789 template <class S>
790 V8_INLINE Global(Isolate* isolate, const PersistentBase<S>& that)
791 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, that.val_)) {
792 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
793 }
797 V8_INLINE Global(Global&& other) : PersistentBase<T>(other.val_) { // NOLINT
798 other.val_ = nullptr;
799 }
800 V8_INLINE ~Global() { this->Reset(); }
804 template <class S>
805 V8_INLINE Global& operator=(Global<S>&& rhs) { // NOLINT
806 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
807 if (this != &rhs) {
808 this->Reset();
809 this->val_ = rhs.val_;
810 rhs.val_ = nullptr;
811 }
812 return *this;
813 }
817 Global Pass() { return static_cast<Global&&>(*this); } // NOLINT
818
819 /*
820 * For compatibility with Chromium's base::Bind (base::Passed).
821 */
822 typedef void MoveOnlyTypeForCPP03;
823
824 Global(const Global&) = delete;
825 void operator=(const Global&) = delete;
826
827 private:
828 template <class F>
829 friend class ReturnValue;
830 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
831};

962class ScriptOriginOptions {
963 public:
964 V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(bool is_shared_cross_origin = false,
965 bool is_opaque = false, bool is_wasm = false)
966 : flags_((is_shared_cross_origin ? kIsSharedCrossOrigin : 0) |
967 (is_wasm ? kIsWasm : 0) | (is_opaque ? kIsOpaque : 0)) {}
968 V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(int flags)
969 : flags_(flags & (kIsSharedCrossOrigin | kIsOpaque | kIsWasm)) {}
970 bool IsSharedCrossOrigin() const {
971 return (flags_ & kIsSharedCrossOrigin) != 0;
972 }
973 bool IsOpaque() const { return (flags_ & kIsOpaque) != 0; }
974 bool IsWasm() const { return (flags_ & kIsWasm) != 0; }
975 int Flags() const { return flags_; }
976
977 private:
978 enum { kIsSharedCrossOrigin = 1, kIsOpaque = 1 << 1, kIsWasm = 1 << 2 };
979 const int flags_;
980};

985class ScriptOrigin {
986 public:
987 V8_INLINE ScriptOrigin(
988 Local<Value> resource_name,
989 Local<Integer> resource_line_offset = Local<Integer>(),
990 Local<Integer> resource_column_offset = Local<Integer>(),
991 Local<Boolean> resource_is_shared_cross_origin = Local<Boolean>(),
992 Local<Integer> script_id = Local<Integer>(),
993 Local<Value> source_map_url = Local<Value>(),
994 Local<Boolean> resource_is_opaque = Local<Boolean>(),
995 Local<Boolean> is_wasm = Local<Boolean>());
996
997 V8_INLINE Local<Value> ResourceName() const;
998 V8_INLINE Local<Integer> ResourceLineOffset() const;
999 V8_INLINE Local<Integer> ResourceColumnOffset() const;
1003 V8_INLINE Local<Integer> ScriptID() const;
1004 V8_INLINE Local<Value> SourceMapUrl() const;
1005 V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions Options() const { return options_; }
1006
1007 private:
1008 Local<Value> resource_name_;
1009 Local<Integer> resource_line_offset_;

1129class V8_EXPORT ScriptCompiler {
1130 public:
1138 struct V8_EXPORT CachedData {
1139 enum BufferPolicy {
1140 BufferNotOwned,
1141 BufferOwned
1142 };
1143
1144 CachedData()
1145 : data(NULL),
1146 length(0),
1147 rejected(false),
1148 buffer_policy(BufferNotOwned) {}
1149
1150 // If buffer_policy is BufferNotOwned, the caller keeps the ownership of
1151 // data and guarantees that it stays alive until the CachedData object is
1152 // destroyed. If the policy is BufferOwned, the given data will be deleted
1153 // (with delete[]) when the CachedData object is destroyed.
1154 CachedData(const uint8_t* data, int length,
1155 BufferPolicy buffer_policy = BufferNotOwned);
1156 ~CachedData();
1157 // TODO(marja): Async compilation; add constructors which take a callback
1158 // which will be called when V8 no longer needs the data.
1159 const uint8_t* data;
1160 int length;
1161 bool rejected;
1162 BufferPolicy buffer_policy;
1163
1164 // Prevent copying.
1165 CachedData(const CachedData&) = delete;
1166 CachedData& operator=(const CachedData&) = delete;
1167 };
1168
1172 class Source {
1173 public:
1174 // Source takes ownership of CachedData.
1175 V8_INLINE Source(Local<String> source_string, const ScriptOrigin& origin,
1176 CachedData* cached_data = NULL);
1177 V8_INLINE Source(Local<String> source_string,
1178 CachedData* cached_data = NULL);
1179 V8_INLINE ~Source();
1180
1181 // Ownership of the CachedData or its buffers is *not* transferred to the
1182 // caller. The CachedData object is alive as long as the Source object is
1183 // alive.
1184 V8_INLINE const CachedData* GetCachedData() const;
1185
1186 // Prevent copying.
1187 Source(const Source&) = delete;
1188 Source& operator=(const Source&) = delete;
1189
1190 private:
1191 friend class ScriptCompiler;
1192
1193 Local<String> source_string;
1194
1195 // Origin information
1196 Local<Value> resource_name;
1197 Local<Integer> resource_line_offset;
1198 Local<Integer> resource_column_offset;
1199 ScriptOriginOptions resource_options;
1200 Local<Value> source_map_url;
1201
1202 // Cached data from previous compilation (if a kConsume*Cache flag is
1203 // set), or hold newly generated cache data (kProduce*Cache flags) are
1204 // set when calling a compile method.
1205 CachedData* cached_data;
1206 };

1632// A StateTag represents a possible state of the VM.
1633enum StateTag { JS, GC, COMPILER, OTHER, EXTERNAL, IDLE };
1634
1635// A RegisterState represents the current state of registers used
1636// by the sampling profiler API.
1637struct RegisterState {
1638 RegisterState() : pc(nullptr), sp(nullptr), fp(nullptr) {}
1639 void* pc; // Instruction pointer.
1640 void* sp; // Stack pointer.
1641 void* fp; // Frame pointer.
1642};
1643
1644// The output structure filled up by GetStackSample API function.
1645struct SampleInfo {
1646 size_t frames_count; // Number of frames collected.
1647 StateTag vm_state; // Current VM state.

1649 // executing an external callback.

1692class V8_EXPORT ValueSerializer {
1693 public:
1694 class V8_EXPORT Delegate {
1695 public:
1696 virtual ~Delegate() {}
1697
1698 /*
1699 * Handles the case where a DataCloneError would be thrown in the structured
1700 * clone spec. Other V8 embedders may throw some other appropriate exception
1701 * type.
1702 */
1703 virtual void ThrowDataCloneError(Local<String> message) = 0;
1704
1705 /*
1706 * The embedder overrides this method to write some kind of host object, if
1707 * possible. If not, a suitable exception should be thrown and
1708 * Nothing<bool>() returned.
1709 */
1710 virtual Maybe<bool> WriteHostObject(Isolate* isolate, Local<Object> object);
1711
1712 /*
1713 * Called when the ValueSerializer is going to serialize a
1714 * SharedArrayBuffer object. The embedder must return an ID for the
1715 * object, using the same ID if this SharedArrayBuffer has already been
1716 * serialized in this buffer. When deserializing, this ID will be passed to
1717 * ValueDeserializer::TransferSharedArrayBuffer as |transfer_id|.
1718 *
1719 * If the object cannot be serialized, an
1720 * exception should be thrown and Nothing<uint32_t>() returned.
1721 */
1722 virtual Maybe<uint32_t> GetSharedArrayBufferId(
1723 Isolate* isolate, Local<SharedArrayBuffer> shared_array_buffer);
1724
1725 /*
1726 * Allocates memory for the buffer of at least the size provided. The actual
1727 * size (which may be greater or equal) is written to |actual_size|. If no
1728 * buffer has been allocated yet, nullptr will be provided.
1729 */
1730 virtual void* ReallocateBufferMemory(void* old_buffer, size_t size,
1731 size_t* actual_size);
1732
1733 /*
1734 * Frees a buffer allocated with |ReallocateBufferMemory|.
1735 */
1736 virtual void FreeBufferMemory(void* buffer);
1737 };
1738
1739 explicit ValueSerializer(Isolate* isolate);
1740 ValueSerializer(Isolate* isolate, Delegate* delegate);
1741 ~ValueSerializer();
1742
1743 /*
1744 * Writes out a header, which includes the format version.
1745 */
1746 void WriteHeader();
1747
1748 /*
1749 * Serializes a JavaScript value into the buffer.
1750 */
1751 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT Maybe<bool> WriteValue(Local<Context> context,
1752 Local<Value> value);
1753
1754 /*
1755 * Returns the stored data. This serializer should not be used once the buffer
1756 * is released. The contents are undefined if a previous write has failed.
1757 */
1758 V8_DEPRECATE_SOON("Use Release()", std::vector<uint8_t> ReleaseBuffer());
1759
1760 /*
1761 * Returns the stored data (allocated using the delegate's
1762 * AllocateBufferMemory) and its size. This serializer should not be used once
1763 * the buffer is released. The contents are undefined if a previous write has
1764 * failed.
1765 */
1766 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT std::pair<uint8_t*, size_t> Release();
1767
1768 /*
1769 * Marks an ArrayBuffer as havings its contents transferred out of band.
1770 * Pass the corresponding JSArrayBuffer in the deserializing context to
1771 * ValueDeserializer::TransferArrayBuffer.
1772 */
1773 void TransferArrayBuffer(uint32_t transfer_id,
1774 Local<ArrayBuffer> array_buffer);
1775
1776 /*
1777 * Similar to TransferArrayBuffer, but for SharedArrayBuffer.
1778 */
1779 V8_DEPRECATE_SOON("Use Delegate::GetSharedArrayBufferId",
1780 void TransferSharedArrayBuffer(
1781 uint32_t transfer_id,
1782 Local<SharedArrayBuffer> shared_array_buffer));
1783
1784 /*
1785 * Write raw data in various common formats to the buffer.
1786 * Note that integer types are written in base-128 varint format, not with a
1787 * binary copy. For use during an override of Delegate::WriteHostObject.
1788 */
1789 void WriteUint32(uint32_t value);
1790 void WriteUint64(uint64_t value);
1791 void WriteDouble(double value);
1792 void WriteRawBytes(const void* source, size_t length);
1793
1794 private:
1795 ValueSerializer(const ValueSerializer&) = delete;
1796 void operator=(const ValueSerializer&) = delete;
1797
1798 struct PrivateData;
1799 PrivateData* private_;
1800};

1810class V8_EXPORT ValueDeserializer {
1811 public:
1812 class V8_EXPORT Delegate {
1813 public:
1814 virtual ~Delegate() {}
1815
1816 /*
1817 * The embedder overrides this method to read some kind of host object, if
1818 * possible. If not, a suitable exception should be thrown and
1819 * MaybeLocal<Object>() returned.
1820 */
1821 virtual MaybeLocal<Object> ReadHostObject(Isolate* isolate);
1822 };
1823
1824 ValueDeserializer(Isolate* isolate, const uint8_t* data, size_t size);
1825 ValueDeserializer(Isolate* isolate, const uint8_t* data, size_t size,
1826 Delegate* delegate);
1827 ~ValueDeserializer();
1828
1829 /*
1830 * Reads and validates a header (including the format version).
1831 * May, for example, reject an invalid or unsupported wire format.
1832 */
1833 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT Maybe<bool> ReadHeader(Local<Context> context);
1834
1835 /*
1836 * Deserializes a JavaScript value from the buffer.
1837 */
1838 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT MaybeLocal<Value> ReadValue(Local<Context> context);
1839
1840 /*
1841 * Accepts the array buffer corresponding to the one passed previously to
1842 * ValueSerializer::TransferArrayBuffer.
1843 */
1844 void TransferArrayBuffer(uint32_t transfer_id,
1845 Local<ArrayBuffer> array_buffer);
1846
1847 /*
1848 * Similar to TransferArrayBuffer, but for SharedArrayBuffer.
1849 * The id is not necessarily in the same namespace as unshared ArrayBuffer
1850 * objects.
1851 */
1852 void TransferSharedArrayBuffer(uint32_t id,
1853 Local<SharedArrayBuffer> shared_array_buffer);
1854
1855 /*
1856 * Must be called before ReadHeader to enable support for reading the legacy
1857 * wire format (i.e., which predates this being shipped).
1858 *
1859 * Don't use this unless you need to read data written by previous versions of
1860 * blink::ScriptValueSerializer.
1861 */
1862 void SetSupportsLegacyWireFormat(bool supports_legacy_wire_format);
1863
1864 /*
1865 * Reads the underlying wire format version. Likely mostly to be useful to
1866 * legacy code reading old wire format versions. Must be called after
1867 * ReadHeader.
1868 */
1869 uint32_t GetWireFormatVersion() const;
1870
1871 /*
1872 * Reads raw data in various common formats to the buffer.
1873 * Note that integer types are read in base-128 varint format, not with a
1874 * binary copy. For use during an override of Delegate::ReadHostObject.
1875 */
1876 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT bool ReadUint32(uint32_t* value);
1877 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT bool ReadUint64(uint64_t* value);
1878 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT bool ReadDouble(double* value);
1879 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT bool ReadRawBytes(size_t length, const void** data);
1880
1881 private:
1882 ValueDeserializer(const ValueDeserializer&) = delete;
1883 void operator=(const ValueDeserializer&) = delete;
1884
1885 struct PrivateData;
1886 PrivateData* private_;
1887};

2676class V8_EXPORT Symbol : public Name {
2677 public:
2678 // Returns the print name string of the symbol, or undefined if none.
2679 Local<Value> Name() const;
2680
2681 // Create a symbol. If name is not empty, it will be used as the description.
2682 static Local<Symbol> New(Isolate* isolate,
2683 Local<String> name = Local<String>());
2684
2685 // Access global symbol registry.
2686 // Note that symbols created this way are never collected, so
2687 // they should only be used for statically fixed properties.
2688 // Also, there is only one global name space for the names used as keys.
2689 // To minimize the potential for clashes, use qualified names as keys.
2690 static Local<Symbol> For(Isolate *isolate, Local<String> name);
2691
2692 // Retrieve a global symbol. Similar to |For|, but using a separate
2693 // registry that is not accessible by (and cannot clash with) JavaScript code.
2694 static Local<Symbol> ForApi(Isolate *isolate, Local<String> name);
2695
2696 // Well-known symbols
2697 static Local<Symbol> GetIterator(Isolate* isolate);
2698 static Local<Symbol> GetUnscopables(Isolate* isolate);
2699 static Local<Symbol> GetToPrimitive(Isolate* isolate);
2700 static Local<Symbol> GetToStringTag(Isolate* isolate);
2701 static Local<Symbol> GetIsConcatSpreadable(Isolate* isolate);
2702
2703 V8_INLINE static Symbol* Cast(Value* obj);
2704
2705 private:
2706 Symbol();
2707 static void CheckCast(Value* obj);
2708};

2716class V8_EXPORT Private : public Data {

2718 // Returns the print name string of the private symbol, or undefined if none.
2719 Local<Value> Name() const;
2720
2721 // Create a private symbol. If name is not empty, it will be the description.
2722 static Local<Private> New(Isolate* isolate,
2723 Local<String> name = Local<String>());
2724
2725 // Retrieve a global private symbol. If a symbol with this name has not
2726 // been retrieved in the same isolate before, it is created.
2727 // Note that private symbols created this way are never collected, so
2728 // they should only be used for statically fixed properties.
2729 // Also, there is only one global name space for the names used as keys.
2730 // To minimize the potential for clashes, use qualified names as keys,
2731 // e.g., "Class#property".
2732 static Local<Private> ForApi(Isolate* isolate, Local<String> name);

2897 // Defines a configurable, writable, enumerable property with the given value
2898 // on the object unless the property already exists and is not configurable
2899 // or the object is not extensible.

2919 // Implements Object.DefineProperty(O, P, Attributes), see Ecma-262 19.1.2.4.
2920 //
2921 // The defineProperty function is used to add an own property or
2922 // update the attributes of an existing own property of an object.
2923 //
2924 // Both data and accessor descriptors can be used.
2925 //
2926 // In general, CreateDataProperty is faster, however, does not allow
2927 // for specifying attributes or an accessor descriptor.
2928 //
2929 // The PropertyDescriptor can change when redefining a property.
2930 //
2931 // Returns true on success.

2935 // Sets an own property on this object bypassing interceptors and
2936 // overriding accessors or read-only properties.
2937 //
2938 // Note that if the object has an interceptor the property will be set
2939 // locally, but since the interceptor takes precedence the local property
2940 // will only be returned if the interceptor doesn't return a value.
2941 //
2942 // Note also that this only works for named properties.

2944 bool ForceSet(Local<Value> key, Local<Value> value,
2945 PropertyAttribute attribs = None));
2946 V8_DEPRECATE_SOON("Use CreateDataProperty / DefineOwnProperty",
2947 Maybe<bool> ForceSet(Local<Context> context,

2949 PropertyAttribute attribs = None));

3419template<typename T>
3420class ReturnValue {
3421 public:
3422 template <class S> V8_INLINE ReturnValue(const ReturnValue<S>& that)
3423 : value_(that.value_) {
3424 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
3425 }
3426 // Local setters
3427 template <typename S>
3428 V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATE_SOON("Use Global<> instead",
3429 void Set(const Persistent<S>& handle));
3430 template <typename S>
3431 V8_INLINE void Set(const Global<S>& handle);
3432 template <typename S>
3433 V8_INLINE void Set(const Local<S> handle);
3434 // Fast primitive setters
3435 V8_INLINE void Set(bool value);
3436 V8_INLINE void Set(double i);
3437 V8_INLINE void Set(int32_t i);
3438 V8_INLINE void Set(uint32_t i);
3439 // Fast JS primitive setters
3440 V8_INLINE void SetNull();
3441 V8_INLINE void SetUndefined();
3442 V8_INLINE void SetEmptyString();
3443 // Convenience getter for Isolate
3444 V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const;
3445
3446 // Pointer setter: Uncompilable to prevent inadvertent misuse.
3447 template <typename S>
3448 V8_INLINE void Set(S* whatever);
3449
3450 // Getter. Creates a new Local<> so it comes with a certain performance
3451 // hit. If the ReturnValue was not yet set, this will return the undefined
3452 // value.
3453 V8_INLINE Local<Value> Get() const;
3454
3455 private:
3456 template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
3457 template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
3458 template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
3459 template <class F, class G, class H>
3460 friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
3461 V8_INLINE void SetInternal(internal::Object* value) { *value_ = value; }
3462 V8_INLINE internal::Object* GetDefaultValue();
3463 V8_INLINE explicit ReturnValue(internal::Object** slot);
3464 internal::Object** value_;
3465};

6091struct JitCodeEvent {
6092 enum EventType {
6093 CODE_ADDED,
6094 CODE_MOVED,
6095 CODE_REMOVED,
6096 CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO,
6097 CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING,
6098 CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING
6099 };
6100 // Definition of the code position type. The "POSITION" type means the place
6101 // in the source code which are of interest when making stack traces to
6102 // pin-point the source location of a stack frame as close as possible.
6103 // The "STATEMENT_POSITION" means the place at the beginning of each
6104 // statement, and is used to indicate possible break locations.
6105 enum PositionType { POSITION, STATEMENT_POSITION };
6106
6107 // Type of event.
6108 EventType type;
6109 // Start of the instructions.
6110 void* code_start;
6111 // Size of the instructions.
6112 size_t code_len;
6113 // Script info for CODE_ADDED event.
6114 Local<UnboundScript> script;
6115 // User-defined data for *_LINE_INFO_* event. It's used to hold the source
6116 // code line information which is returned from the
6117 // CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING event. And it's passed to subsequent
6118 // CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO and CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING events.
6119 void* user_data;
6120
6121 struct name_t {
6122 // Name of the object associated with the code, note that the string is not
6123 // zero-terminated.
6124 const char* str;
6125 // Number of chars in str.
6126 size_t len;
6127 };
6128
6129 struct line_info_t {
6130 // PC offset
6131 size_t offset;
6132 // Code postion
6133 size_t pos;
6134 // The position type.
6135 PositionType position_type;
6136 };
6137
6138 union {
6139 // Only valid for CODE_ADDED.
6140 struct name_t name;
6141
6142 // Only valid for CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO
6143 struct line_info_t line_info;
6144
6145 // New location of instructions. Only valid for CODE_MOVED.
6146 void* new_code_start;
6147 };
6148};
6149
6155enum RAILMode {
6156 // Response performance mode: In this mode very low virtual machine latency
6157 // is provided. V8 will try to avoid JavaScript execution interruptions.
6158 // Throughput may be throttled.
6159 PERFORMANCE_RESPONSE,
6160 // Animation performance mode: In this mode low virtual machine latency is
6161 // provided. V8 will try to avoid as many JavaScript execution interruptions
6162 // as possible. Throughput may be throttled. This is the default mode.
6163 PERFORMANCE_ANIMATION,
6164 // Idle performance mode: The embedder is idle. V8 can complete deferred work
6165 // in this mode.
6166 PERFORMANCE_IDLE,
6167 // Load performance mode: In this mode high throughput is provided. V8 may
6168 // turn off latency optimizations.
6169 PERFORMANCE_LOAD
6170};
6171
6175enum JitCodeEventOptions {
6176 kJitCodeEventDefault = 0,
6177 // Generate callbacks for already existent code.
6178 kJitCodeEventEnumExisting = 1
6179};
6180
6181
6187typedef void (*JitCodeEventHandler)(const JitCodeEvent* event);

7777template <class T>
7778class Maybe {
7779 public:
7780 V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !has_value_; }
7781 V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return has_value_; }
7782
7783 // Will crash if the Maybe<> is nothing.
7784 V8_INLINE T ToChecked() const { return FromJust(); }
7785
7786 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool To(T* out) const {
7787 if (V8_LIKELY(IsJust())) *out = value_;
7788 return IsJust();
7789 }
7790
7791 // Will crash if the Maybe<> is nothing.
7792 V8_INLINE T FromJust() const {
7793 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
7794 return value_;
7795 }
7796
7797 V8_INLINE T FromMaybe(const T& default_value) const {
7798 return has_value_ ? value_ : default_value;
7799 }
7800
7801 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
7802 return (IsJust() == other.IsJust()) &&
7803 (!IsJust() || FromJust() == other.FromJust());
7804 }
7805
7806 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
7807 return !operator==(other);
7808 }
7809
7810 private:
7811 Maybe() : has_value_(false) {}
7812 explicit Maybe(const T& t) : has_value_(true), value_(t) {}
7813
7814 bool has_value_;
7815 T value_;
7816
7817 template <class U>
7818 friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
7819 template <class U>
7820 friend Maybe<U> Just(const U& u);
7821};
7822
7823
7824template <class T>
7825inline Maybe<T> Nothing() {
7826 return Maybe<T>();
7827}
7828
7829
7830template <class T>
7831inline Maybe<T> Just(const T& t) {
7832 return Maybe<T>(t);
7833}

8366namespace internal {
8367
8368const int kApiPointerSize = sizeof(void*); // NOLINT
8369const int kApiIntSize = sizeof(int); // NOLINT
8370const int kApiInt64Size = sizeof(int64_t); // NOLINT
8371
8372// Tag information for HeapObject.
8373const int kHeapObjectTag = 1;
8374const int kHeapObjectTagSize = 2;
8375const intptr_t kHeapObjectTagMask = (1 << kHeapObjectTagSize) - 1;
8376
8377// Tag information for Smi.
8378const int kSmiTag = 0;
8379const int kSmiTagSize = 1;
8380const intptr_t kSmiTagMask = (1 << kSmiTagSize) - 1;
8381
8382template <size_t ptr_size> struct SmiTagging;
8383
8384template<int kSmiShiftSize>
8385V8_INLINE internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
8386 int smi_shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
8387 uintptr_t tagged_value =
8388 (static_cast<uintptr_t>(value) << smi_shift_bits) | kSmiTag;
8389 return reinterpret_cast<internal::Object*>(tagged_value);
8390}
8391
8392// Smi constants for 32-bit systems.
8393template <> struct SmiTagging<4> {
8394 enum { kSmiShiftSize = 0, kSmiValueSize = 31 };
8395 static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
8396 static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
8397 V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
8398 int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
8399 // Throw away top 32 bits and shift down (requires >> to be sign extending).
8400 return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value)) >> shift_bits;
8401 }
8402 V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
8403 return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
8404 }
8405 V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
8406 // To be representable as an tagged small integer, the two
8407 // most-significant bits of 'value' must be either 00 or 11 due to
8408 // sign-extension. To check this we add 01 to the two
8409 // most-significant bits, and check if the most-significant bit is 0
8410 //
8411 // CAUTION: The original code below:
8412 // bool result = ((value + 0x40000000) & 0x80000000) == 0;
8413 // may lead to incorrect results according to the C language spec, and
8414 // in fact doesn't work correctly with gcc4.1.1 in some cases: The
8415 // compiler may produce undefined results in case of signed integer
8416 // overflow. The computation must be done w/ unsigned ints.
8417 return static_cast<uintptr_t>(value + 0x40000000U) < 0x80000000U;
8418 }
8419};
8420
8421// Smi constants for 64-bit systems.
8422template <> struct SmiTagging<8> {
8423 enum { kSmiShiftSize = 31, kSmiValueSize = 32 };
8424 static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
8425 static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
8426 V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
8427 int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
8428 // Shift down and throw away top 32 bits.
8429 return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value) >> shift_bits);
8430 }
8431 V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
8432 return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
8433 }
8434 V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
8435 // To be representable as a long smi, the value must be a 32-bit integer.
8436 return (value == static_cast<int32_t>(value));
8437 }
8438};
8439
8440typedef SmiTagging<kApiPointerSize> PlatformSmiTagging;
8441const int kSmiShiftSize = PlatformSmiTagging::kSmiShiftSize;
8442const int kSmiValueSize = PlatformSmiTagging::kSmiValueSize;
8443V8_INLINE static bool SmiValuesAre31Bits() { return kSmiValueSize == 31; }
8444V8_INLINE static bool SmiValuesAre32Bits() { return kSmiValueSize == 32; }

8451class Internals {

8460 static const int kOddballKindOffset = 4 * kApiPointerSize + sizeof(double);

8463 static const int kFixedArrayHeaderSize = 2 * kApiPointerSize;

8469 static const int kExternalOneByteRepresentationTag = 0x06;

8488 static const int kNodeStateIsWeakValue = 2;

8512 V8_INLINE static bool HasHeapObjectTag(const internal::Object* value) {
8513 return ((reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value) & kHeapObjectTagMask) ==
8514 kHeapObjectTag);
8515 }

8529 V8_INLINE static int GetInstanceType(const internal::Object* obj) {
8530 typedef internal::Object O;
8531 O* map = ReadField<O*>(obj, kHeapObjectMapOffset);
8532 // Map::InstanceType is defined so that it will always be loaded into
8533 // the LS 8 bits of one 16-bit word, regardless of endianess.
8534 return ReadField<uint16_t>(map, kMapInstanceTypeAndBitFieldOffset) & 0xff;
8535 }
8536
8537 V8_INLINE static int GetOddballKind(const internal::Object* obj) {
8538 typedef internal::Object O;
8539 return SmiValue(ReadField<O*>(obj, kOddballKindOffset));
8540 }

8542 V8_INLINE static bool IsExternalTwoByteString(int instance_type) {
8543 int representation = (instance_type & kFullStringRepresentationMask);
8544 return representation == kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag;
8545 }
8546
8547 V8_INLINE static uint8_t GetNodeFlag(internal::Object** obj, int shift) {
8548 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
8549 return *addr & static_cast<uint8_t>(1U << shift);
8550 }
8551
8552 V8_INLINE static void UpdateNodeFlag(internal::Object** obj,
8553 bool value, int shift) {
8554 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
8555 uint8_t mask = static_cast<uint8_t>(1U << shift);
8556 *addr = static_cast<uint8_t>((*addr & ~mask) | (value << shift));
8557 }
8558
8559 V8_INLINE static uint8_t GetNodeState(internal::Object** obj) {
8560 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
8561 return *addr & kNodeStateMask;
8562 }
8563
8564 V8_INLINE static void UpdateNodeState(internal::Object** obj,
8565 uint8_t value) {
8566 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
8567 *addr = static_cast<uint8_t>((*addr & ~kNodeStateMask) | value);
8568 }

8570 V8_INLINE static void SetEmbedderData(v8::Isolate* isolate,
8571 uint32_t slot,
8572 void* data) {
8573 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(isolate) +
8574 kIsolateEmbedderDataOffset + slot * kApiPointerSize;
8575 *reinterpret_cast<void**>(addr) = data;
8576 }
8577
8578 V8_INLINE static void* GetEmbedderData(const v8::Isolate* isolate,
8579 uint32_t slot) {
8580 const uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(isolate) +
8581 kIsolateEmbedderDataOffset + slot * kApiPointerSize;
8582 return *reinterpret_cast<void* const*>(addr);
8583 }
8584
8585 V8_INLINE static internal::Object** GetRoot(v8::Isolate* isolate,
8586 int index) {
8587 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(isolate) + kIsolateRootsOffset;
8588 return reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(addr + index * kApiPointerSize);
8589 }
8590
8591 template <typename T>
8592 V8_INLINE static T ReadField(const internal::Object* ptr, int offset) {
8593 const uint8_t* addr =
8594 reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(ptr) + offset - kHeapObjectTag;
8595 return *reinterpret_cast<const T*>(addr);
8596 }
8597
8598 template <typename T>
8599 V8_INLINE static T ReadEmbedderData(const v8::Context* context, int index) {
8600 typedef internal::Object O;
8601 typedef internal::Internals I;
8602 O* ctx = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(context);
8603 int embedder_data_offset = I::kContextHeaderSize +
8604 (internal::kApiPointerSize * I::kContextEmbedderDataIndex);
8605 O* embedder_data = I::ReadField<O*>(ctx, embedder_data_offset);
8606 int value_offset =
8607 I::kFixedArrayHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
8608 return I::ReadField<T>(embedder_data, value_offset);
8609 }
8610};

8656
8657template <class T>
8658void* WeakCallbackInfo<T>::GetInternalField(int index) const {
8659#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
8660 if (index < 0 || index >= kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback) {
8661 V8::InternalFieldOutOfBounds(index);
8662 }
8663#endif
8664 return internal_fields_[index];
8665}
8666
8667
8668template <class T>
8669T* PersistentBase<T>::New(Isolate* isolate, T* that) {
8670 if (that == NULL) return NULL;
8671 internal::Object** p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that);
8672 return reinterpret_cast<T*>(
8673 V8::GlobalizeReference(reinterpret_cast<internal::Isolate*>(isolate),
8674 p));
8675}
8676
8677
8678template <class T, class M>
8679template <class S, class M2>
8680void Persistent<T, M>::Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) {
8681 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
8682 this->Reset();
8683 if (that.IsEmpty()) return;
8684 internal::Object** p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
8685 this->val_ = reinterpret_cast<T*>(V8::CopyPersistent(p));
8686 M::Copy(that, this);
8687}

8690template <class T>
8691bool PersistentBase<T>::IsIndependent() const {
8692 typedef internal::Internals I;
8693 if (this->IsEmpty()) return false;
8694 return I::GetNodeFlag(reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_),
8695 I::kNodeIsIndependentShift);
8696}
8697
8698
8699template <class T>
8700bool PersistentBase<T>::IsNearDeath() const {
8701 typedef internal::Internals I;
8702 if (this->IsEmpty()) return false;
8703 uint8_t node_state =
8704 I::GetNodeState(reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_));
8705 return node_state == I::kNodeStateIsNearDeathValue ||
8706 node_state == I::kNodeStateIsPendingValue;
8707}
8708
8709
8710template <class T>
8711bool PersistentBase<T>::IsWeak() const {
8712 typedef internal::Internals I;
8713 if (this->IsEmpty()) return false;
8714 return I::GetNodeState(reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_)) ==
8715 I::kNodeStateIsWeakValue;
8716}

8718
8719template <class T>
8720void PersistentBase<T>::Reset() {
8721 if (this->IsEmpty()) return;
8722 V8::DisposeGlobal(reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_));
8723 val_ = 0;
8724}
8725

8727template <class T>
8728template <class S>
8729void PersistentBase<T>::Reset(Isolate* isolate, const Local<S>& other) {
8730 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
8731 Reset();
8732 if (other.IsEmpty()) return;
8733 this->val_ = New(isolate, other.val_);
8734}
8735
8736
8737template <class T>
8738template <class S>
8739void PersistentBase<T>::Reset(Isolate* isolate,
8740 const PersistentBase<S>& other) {
8741 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
8742 Reset();
8743 if (other.IsEmpty()) return;
8744 this->val_ = New(isolate, other.val_);
8745}

8751 P* parameter, typename WeakCallbackInfo<P>::Callback callback,
8752 WeakCallbackType type) {
8753 typedef typename WeakCallbackInfo<void>::Callback Callback;
8754 V8::MakeWeak(reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_), parameter,
8755 reinterpret_cast<Callback>(callback), type);
8756}

8760 V8::MakeWeak(reinterpret_cast<internal::Object***>(&this->val_));

8767 V8::ClearWeak(reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_)));

8783 true,
8784 I::kNodeIsIndependentShift);
8785}

8791 I::UpdateNodeFlag(reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_), true,
8792 I::kNodeIsActiveShift);

8796template <class T>
8797void PersistentBase<T>::SetWrapperClassId(uint16_t class_id) {
8798 typedef internal::Internals I;
8799 if (this->IsEmpty()) return;
8800 internal::Object** obj = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
8801 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + I::kNodeClassIdOffset;
8802 *reinterpret_cast<uint16_t*>(addr) = class_id;
8803}

8805
8806template <class T>
8807uint16_t PersistentBase<T>::WrapperClassId() const {
8808 typedef internal::Internals I;
8809 if (this->IsEmpty()) return 0;
8810 internal::Object** obj = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
8811 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + I::kNodeClassIdOffset;
8812 return *reinterpret_cast<uint16_t*>(addr);
8813}

8852template<typename T>
8853void ReturnValue<T>::Set(double i) {
8854 TYPE_CHECK(T, Number);
8855 Set(Number::New(GetIsolate(), i));
8856}
8857
8858template<typename T>
8859void ReturnValue<T>::Set(int32_t i) {
8860 TYPE_CHECK(T, Integer);
8861 typedef internal::Internals I;
8862 if (V8_LIKELY(I::IsValidSmi(i))) {
8863 *value_ = I::IntToSmi(i);
8864 return;
8865 }
8866 Set(Integer::New(GetIsolate(), i));
8867}
8868
8869template<typename T>
8870void ReturnValue<T>::Set(uint32_t i) {
8871 TYPE_CHECK(T, Integer);
8872 // Can't simply use INT32_MAX here for whatever reason.
8873 bool fits_into_int32_t = (i & (1U << 31)) == 0;
8874 if (V8_LIKELY(fits_into_int32_t)) {
8875 Set(static_cast<int32_t>(i));
8876 return;
8877 }
8878 Set(Integer::NewFromUnsigned(GetIsolate(), i));
8879}
8880
8881template<typename T>
8882void ReturnValue<T>::Set(bool value) {
8883 TYPE_CHECK(T, Boolean);
8884 typedef internal::Internals I;
8885 int root_index;
8886 if (value) {
8887 root_index = I::kTrueValueRootIndex;
8888 } else {
8889 root_index = I::kFalseValueRootIndex;
8890 }
8891 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), root_index);
8892}

8894template<typename T>
8895void ReturnValue<T>::SetNull() {
8896 TYPE_CHECK(T, Primitive);
8897 typedef internal::Internals I;
8898 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kNullValueRootIndex);
8899}

8902void ReturnValue<T>::SetUndefined() {
8903 TYPE_CHECK(T, Primitive);
8904 typedef internal::Internals I;
8905 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kUndefinedValueRootIndex);
8906}

8915template <typename T>
8916Isolate* ReturnValue<T>::GetIsolate() const {
8917 // Isolate is always the pointer below the default value on the stack.
8918 return *reinterpret_cast<Isolate**>(&value_[-2]);
8919}

8921template <typename T>
8922Local<Value> ReturnValue<T>::Get() const {
8923 typedef internal::Internals I;
8924 if (*value_ == *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kTheHoleValueRootIndex))
8925 return Local<Value>(*Undefined(GetIsolate()));
8926 return Local<Value>::New(GetIsolate(), reinterpret_cast<Value*>(value_));
8927}

8933 TYPE_CHECK(S*, Primitive);
8934}

8939 return value_[-1];

9083
9084Local<Value> Object::GetInternalField(int index) {
9085#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
9086 typedef internal::Object O;
9087 typedef internal::HeapObject HO;
9088 typedef internal::Internals I;
9089 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
9090 // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
9091 // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
9092 auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
9093 if (instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
9094 instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType) {
9095 int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
9096 O* value = I::ReadField<O*>(obj, offset);
9097 O** result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(reinterpret_cast<HO*>(obj), value);
9098 return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
9099 }
9100#endif
9101 return SlowGetInternalField(index);
9102}
9103
9104
9105void* Object::GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(int index) {
9106#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
9107 typedef internal::Object O;
9108 typedef internal::Internals I;
9109 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
9110 // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
9111 // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
9112 auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
9113 if (V8_LIKELY(instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
9114 instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType)) {
9115 int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
9116 return I::ReadField<void*>(obj, offset);
9117 }
9118#endif
9119 return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(index);
9120}

9138
9139String::ExternalStringResource* String::GetExternalStringResource() const {
9140 typedef internal::Object O;
9141 typedef internal::Internals I;
9142 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
9143 String::ExternalStringResource* result;
9144 if (I::IsExternalTwoByteString(I::GetInstanceType(obj))) {
9145 void* value = I::ReadField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
9146 result = reinterpret_cast<String::ExternalStringResource*>(value);
9147 } else {
9148 result = NULL;
9149 }
9150#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
9151 VerifyExternalStringResource(result);
9152#endif
9153 return result;
9154}
9155
9156
9157String::ExternalStringResourceBase* String::GetExternalStringResourceBase(
9158 String::Encoding* encoding_out) const {
9159 typedef internal::Object O;
9160 typedef internal::Internals I;
9161 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
9162 int type = I::GetInstanceType(obj) & I::kFullStringRepresentationMask;
9163 *encoding_out = static_cast<Encoding>(type & I::kStringEncodingMask);
9164 ExternalStringResourceBase* resource = NULL;
9165 if (type == I::kExternalOneByteRepresentationTag ||
9166 type == I::kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag) {
9167 void* value = I::ReadField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
9168 resource = static_cast<ExternalStringResourceBase*>(value);
9169 }
9170#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
9171 VerifyExternalStringResourceBase(resource, *encoding_out);
9172#endif
9173 return resource;
9174}

9180#else
9181 return QuickIsUndefined();
9182#endif

9184
9185bool Value::QuickIsUndefined() const {
9186 typedef internal::Object O;
9187 typedef internal::Internals I;
9188 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
9189 if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
9190 if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
9191 return (I::GetOddballKind(obj) == I::kUndefinedOddballKind);
9192}

9195bool Value::IsNull() const {
9196#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
9197 return FullIsNull();
9198#else
9199 return QuickIsNull();
9200#endif
9201}
9202
9203bool Value::QuickIsNull() const {
9204 typedef internal::Object O;
9205 typedef internal::Internals I;
9206 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
9207 if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
9208 if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
9209 return (I::GetOddballKind(obj) == I::kNullOddballKind);
9210}
9211
9212bool Value::IsNullOrUndefined() const {
9213#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
9214 return FullIsNull() || FullIsUndefined();
9215#else
9216 return QuickIsNullOrUndefined();
9217#endif
9218}
9219
9220bool Value::QuickIsNullOrUndefined() const {
9221 typedef internal::Object O;
9222 typedef internal::Internals I;
9223 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
9224 if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
9225 if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
9226 int kind = I::GetOddballKind(obj);
9227 return kind == I::kNullOddballKind || kind == I::kUndefinedOddballKind;
9228}

9241 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
9242 if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
9243 return (I::GetInstanceType(obj) < I::kFirstNonstringType);

9683
9684int64_t Isolate::AdjustAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemory(
9685 int64_t change_in_bytes) {
9686 typedef internal::Internals I;
9687 int64_t* external_memory = reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
9688 reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) + I::kExternalMemoryOffset);
9689 const int64_t external_memory_limit = *reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
9690 reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) + I::kExternalMemoryLimitOffset);
9691 const int64_t amount = *external_memory + change_in_bytes;
9692 *external_memory = amount;
9693 if (change_in_bytes > 0 && amount > external_memory_limit) {
9694 ReportExternalAllocationLimitReached();
9695 }
9696 return *external_memory;
9697}

9726Local<Value> Context::GetEmbedderData(int index) {
9727#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
9728 typedef internal::Object O;
9729 typedef internal::HeapObject HO;
9730 typedef internal::Internals I;
9731 HO* context = *reinterpret_cast<HO**>(this);
9732 O** result =
9733 HandleScope::CreateHandle(context, I::ReadEmbedderData<O*>(this, index));
9734 return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
9735#else
9736 return SlowGetEmbedderData(index);
9737#endif
9738}
